    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1186_s13321_022_00613_8__task_002/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "DNNs were used for Retention Time (RT) prediction in [21], where a DNN with 4 layers and regularization was proposed... we used a DNN with just 3 layers, regularized using large dropout rates. The sizes of the hidden layers, the dropout rates and the non-linear activations were determined using Bayesian hyperparameter search.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes DNN architecture (3 layers, dropout rates, activations) and hyperparameter tuning procedure, but does not provide explicit trained model weights or complete architecture specifications in the passages. Code is available on GitHub but weights are not reported in the paper text.",
