    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1186_s13321_022_00613_8__task_002/scope_drift",
      "@type": "asbval:ScopeDriftAssertion",
      "asbval:drift_notes": [
        "The card's research question is narrowly framed as a comparison of fingerprints vs descriptors, but the paper's actual scope is much broader: it compares multiple machine learning regressors (DNN, DKL, XGBoost, lightGBM, CatBoost, blending ensemble) across three feature sets, and also develops a novel Bayesian meta-learning approach for retention time projection between chromatographic methods. The card captures only one aspect of the paper's contributions.",
        "The expected output about 'trained regression model weights and architecture specification' is partially addressed in the paper (architecture is described) but the paper does not provide explicit weight matrices or complete serialized model specifications in the text\u2014only hyperparameter ranges and architectural choices.",
        "The card does not mention the meta-learning projection method, which is a major contribution of the paper and occupies substantial portions of the methodology and results sections."
      ],
      "asbval:n_drift_notes": 3,
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_002",
