    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1186_s13321_022_00613_8__task_003/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "To build such a projection function, a set of known molecules whos RTs is known in both CMs is needed... To that end, this work proposes a Bayesian meta-learning approach to project the predicted RTs to a specific Chromatographic Method (CM) based on just a few identified molecules. This approach has the advantage of being able to generalize from a small training set while providing confidence intervals for the Retention Time (RT) projections between CMs",
      "asbval:note": "Directly supported by abstract and methods sections",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13321-022-00613-8",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
