    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/retention-time-prediction/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The best results were obtained by a heavily regularized deep neural network trained with cosine annealing warm restarts and stochastic weight averaging, achieving a mean and median absolute errors of [Formula: see text] and [Formula: see text], respectively... a MAE of 39.2 \u00b1 1.2 s when considering all molecules... To project retention times between chromatographic methods, a novel Bayesian meta-learning approach that can learn from just a few molecules is proposed... our approach can be integrated into a metabolite annotation workflow to obtain z-scores for the candidate annotations.",
      "asbval:note": "All core claims verified: DNN architecture, regularization techniques (dropout, cosine annealing, SWA), MAE metric value, and integration into metabolite annotation workflow.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13321-022-00613-8",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
