      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/retention-time-projection-across-chromatographic-methods/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "To project retention times between chromatographic methods, a novel Bayesian meta-learning approach that can learn from just a few molecules is proposed... it is enough that just as few as 10 molecules of a given experiment have been identified",
      "asbval:note": "Paper proposes Bayesian meta-learning for RT projection from few molecules (10+), but the claim about 'mapping to a pre-trained DNN's latent feature space' is not explicitly stated. The paper uses a DNN for RT prediction and then applies a Gaussian Process (GP) for projection, not a direct mapping to DNN latent features. The projection function is a GP, not a latent-space mapping.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13321-022-00613-8",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "retention-time-projection-across-chromatographic-methods",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Project retention times between different chromatographic methods using a Bayesian meta-learning approach that learns a mapping from minimal calibration data (as few as 10 molecules) to a pre-trained DNN's latent feature space.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:00:45.061591+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/retention-time-projection-across-chromatographic-methods/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "in 68% of the cases the correct molecule was among the top three candidates filtered by mass and ranked according to z-scores... When decreasing the number of training points to just 10 samples, the percentage is 68%, while with 30 is 69%",
      "asbval:note": "Paper demonstrates that with as few as 10 training points, the method achieves 68% ranking accuracy, competitive with 70% at 50 training points, supporting the claim of competitive accuracy with minimal calibration.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13321-022-00613-8",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "retention-time-projection-across-chromatographic-methods",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "This enables metabolite annotation and cross-method RT prediction with competitive accuracy relative to larger calibration sets.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:00:45.061591+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/retention-time-projection-across-chromatographic-methods/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "To build such a projection function, a set of known molecules whos RTs is known in both CMs is needed... To use this database, a researcher provides the experimental RTs (as measured in his/her Chromatographic Method (CM)) of a few molecules whose identity is known",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly describes the workflow for projecting RTs between chromatographic methods using calibration molecules.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13321-022-00613-8",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "retention-time-projection-across-chromatographic-methods",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "When you have retention times measured on one chromatographic method and need to predict or map them to another method with minimal or no overlap in measured molecules.",
